                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 4: Market regulator Sebi will issue guidelines on real estate mutual funds in 15 days, enabling retail investors to access the realty market. Sebi is ready with guidelines on real estate mutual funds that could be issued any day. The outer time limit to issue guidelines is 15 days, Sebis whole-time member T.C. Nair said here. All legal issues including accounting and valuation have been resolved. The Sebi board has already approved the guidelines, Nair added.                             
	 New Delhi, April 4: India received $20.13 billion as foreign direct investment (FDI) in April-February 2007-08, a 70 per cent increase from $11.88 billion a year ago. This is the highest FDI into equity in the country during any year, an official release said today.                                                                                                                           
